npm run dev # JSM Custom Configuration

This repository contains the custom configuration for the JSM application. It includes settings for the database connection, JWT token encryption, link formatting, Stripe integration, and more.

## Prerequisites

Before you can use this configuration, you will need to have the following installed:

* Node.js and npm
* MongoDB
* Stripe account

## Installation

To install the dependencies, run the following command in the project directory:

```bash
npm install
```

## Configuration

The configuration is stored in a `.env` file. You can create this file by copying the `.env.example` file and filling in the appropriate values.

The following table describes the configuration options:

| Option | Description |
|---|---|
| `PORT` | The port on which the application will run. |
| `DATABASE_URI` | The connection string for the MongoDB database. |
| `PAYLOAD_SECRET` | The secret used to encrypt JWT tokens. |
| `PAYLOAD_PUBLIC_SERVER_URL` | The public URL of the server. |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_SERVER_URL` | The public URL of the server. |
| `STRIPE_SECRET_KEY` | The secret key for your Stripe account. |
| `PAYLOAD_PUBLIC_STRIPE_IS_TEST_KEY` | Whether or not to use the test key for Stripe. |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_STRIPE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY` | The publishable key for your Stripe account. |
| `STRIPE_WEBHOOKS_SIGNING_SECRET` | The signing secret for Stripe webhooks. |
| `NEXT_PUBLIC_IS_LIVE` | Whether or not the site is live. |
| `PAYLOAD_PUBLIC_DRAFT_SECRET` | The secret used to preview drafts. |
| `NEXT_PRIVATE_DRAFT_SECRET` | The secret used to preview drafts. |
| `REVALIDATION_KEY` | The key used to revalidate static pages. |
| `NEXT_PRIVATE_REVALIDATION_KEY` | The key used to revalidate static pages. |

## Usage

To start the application, run the following command in the project directory:

```bash
npm start
```

The application will then be available at `http://localhost:3000`.

